{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"unixSignalSourceNew"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"signum"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib9SourceRefV","text":"SourceRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that unlike the UNIX default, all sources which have created a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"watch will be dispatched, regardless of which underlying thread"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"invoked "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_unix_signal_source_new()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, an effective use of this function is to handle "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SIGTERM"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"cleanly; flushing any outstanding files, and then calling"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_main_loop_quit()"},{"type":"text","text":".  It is not safe to do any of this from a regular"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"UNIX signal handler; such a handler may be invoked while "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"malloc()"},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"another library function is running, causing reentrancy issues if the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"handler attempts to use those functions.  None of the GLib\/GObject"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"API is safe against this kind of reentrancy."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The interaction of this source when combined with native UNIX"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functions like "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"sigprocmask()"},{"type":"text","text":" is not defined."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The source will not initially be associated with any "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and must be added to one with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_source_attach()"},{"type":"text","text":" before it will be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"executed."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/unixsignalsourcenew(signum:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/unixSignalSourceNew(signum:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source"},{"type":"text","text":" that will be dispatched upon delivery of the UNIX"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"signal "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signum"},{"type":"text","text":".  In GLib versions before 2.36, only "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SIGHUP"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SIGINT"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SIGTERM"},{"type":"text","text":" can be monitored.  In GLib 2.36, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SIGUSR1"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SIGUSR2"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"were added. In GLib 2.54, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SIGWINCH"},{"type":"text","text":" was added."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"fragm